## Key Decisions

### 1. Fibonacci Story Points
**Why:** Industry standard for agile estimation, prevents false precision
**Alternatives considered:** T-shirt sizes (S/M/L), linear scale (1-10)
**Chosen:** Fibonacci for alignment with agile best practices

### 2. Custom Status Labels
**Why:** Needed beyond base Kanban statuses (backlog/todo/inprogress/review/done)
**Options chosen:** In Review, Testing, Deployed, Blocked
**Rationale:** Covers most common PM workflow states

### 3. Time Tracking Storage
**Why:** Task-level tracking (not global TimeTrackingStore)
**Rationale:**
- Tightly coupled to tasks (survives task moves/edits)
- Simpler data model (no cross-store dependencies)
- Better for reporting (all data in one place)

**Note:** TimeTrackingStore still exists for global time tracking (independent of tasks). Phase B adds task-specific tracking.

### 4. Timer Implementation
**Why:** Store timer state in task.timeTracking.activeTimerStart
**Rationale:**
- Persists across page reloads
- Simple boolean check (activeTimerStart !== undefined)
- Duration auto-calculated from start time

### 5. Activity Log Integration
**Why:** Auto-log all field changes (effort, status, timer events)
**Rationale:** Provides audit trail for PM transparency

